definitions.definition: The part of the alimentary canal and respiratory tract that extends from the back of the mouth and nasal cavity to the larynx and esophagus .
The part of the alimentary canal immediately behind the mouth in invertebrates that may be thickened and muscular , eversible and toothed , or adapted as a suctorial organ .

main_definition: ( anatomy ) The part of the alimentary canal and respiratory tract that extends from the back of the mouth and nasal cavity to the larynx and esophagus .
